## {{ rule.title }}

[Form 8949](https://www.irs.gov/forms-pubs/about-form-8949) and [Schedule D](https://www.irs.gov/forms-pubs/about-schedule-d-form-1040) organize every sale of a capital asset by holding period and by reporting box. Box A and Box B hold short-term sales reported by a broker (covered and noncovered); Box H holds short-term sales not reported on a 1099-B (most digital-asset trades). Box D and Box K mirror the long-term side. [26 U.S.C. § 1211](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section1211&num=0&edition=prelim) and [§ 1212](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section1212&num=0&edition=prelim) then key off these buckets to apply the annual loss limit and the carryforward.

{% set buckets = rule.outputs[0].value | from_json -%}
For 2025 the engine sums each bucket as:

- Box A (short-term, covered broker reporting): **{{ buckets.short_box_a_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**
- Box B (short-term, noncovered broker reporting): **{{ buckets.short_box_b_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**
- Box H (short-term, no 1099-B; mostly digital-asset trades): **{{ buckets.short_box_h_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**
- Box D (long-term, covered broker reporting): **{{ buckets.long_box_d_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**
- Box K (long-term, no 1099-B): **{{ buckets.long_box_k_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**
- 1099-DIV box 2a capital-gain distributions (long-term character per [Schedule D](https://www.irs.gov/forms-pubs/about-schedule-d-form-1040) line 13): **{{ buckets.capital_gain_distributions_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**

Aggregating those bands gives short-term **{{ buckets.short_term_total_usd | money(currency="USD") }}** and long-term **{{ buckets.long_term_total_with_cgd_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**, for a pre-[§ 1256](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section1256&num=0&edition=prelim) net of **{{ buckets.net_capital_before_1256_usd | money(currency="USD") }}**.

{% if buckets.digital_asset_transaction_present -%}
At least one digital-asset transaction is present, so the [Form 1040](https://www.irs.gov/forms-pubs/about-form-1040) digital-asset checkbox must be answered "Yes".
{% else -%}
No digital-asset transactions are present in this run, so the [Form 1040](https://www.irs.gov/forms-pubs/about-form-1040) digital-asset checkbox is "No".
{% endif %}

These bucket totals feed the [§ 1256](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section1256&num=0&edition=prelim) character split at US25-04, the [§ 1211(b)](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section1211&num=0&edition=prelim) annual cap at US25-05, and the [§ 1(h)](https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title26-section1&num=0&edition=prelim) preferential base at US25-06.

